A rubbish dump may seem an odd place to seek inspiration, but not for band Fulu Muziki. With a name meaning "music from the garbage", they use what they can find to make their instruments. The band aims to raise awareness of the country's waste and pollution problem. The DR Congo produces around 9 000 tons of rubbish a day. Study finds air pollution may be damaging 'every organ in the body' A comprehensive new global review has found that air pollution may be harming nearly every cell in the human body.According to a review published in Chest Journal, the harmful effects of toxic air begin when it is inhaled. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by
